Facing these challenges has, sometimes, created the yearning for a return to the ‘normal’ past. However, it is important to remember that it is the unsustainable nature of those past models that have brought us to where we are now. 

We cannot deny that the virus found us having weak behavioural and structural systems that enabled its fast transmission and the subsequent adverse effects it has had on the country. 

Crisis moments like this one of the Covid-19 pandemic offer a great opportunity for learning and national transformation. It must not be wasted at all. 

